EU.=[core/form/agt/personal_information/sldavid/map/EU]

Source=GREAT BRITAIN (COP)

Duty.1=Information should be regarded as held for a specific purpose and not to be used, without appropriate authorization, for other purposes.

Duty.2=Access to information should be confined to those authorized to have it for the purpose for which it was supplied.
 
Duty.3=The amount of information collected and held should be the minimum necessary for the achievement of the specified purpose.
 
Duty.4=In computerized systems handling information for statistical purposes, adequate provision should be made in their design and programs for separating identities from the rest of the data.
 
Duty.5=There should be arrangement whereby the subject could be told about the information held concerning him.

Duty.6=The level of security to be achieved by a system should be specified in advance by the user and should include precautions against deliberate abuse or misuse of information.

Duty.7=A monitoring system should be provided to facilitate the detection of any violation of the security system.

Duty.8=In the design of information systems, periods should be specified beyond which the information should not be retained.

Duty.9=Data held should be accurate. There should be machinery for the correction of inaccuracy and the updating of information.

Duty.10=Care should be taken in coding value judgments.

Duty.List={Duty.0-10}<hr>{EU.Duty.List}